"""2D Rendering Engine — Multi-Backend 2D Graphics

@tag:stdlib
@tag:api
@tag:gpu

A multi-backend 2D rendering engine providing an abstract rendering interface.
Each backend implements the same RenderBackend trait. The engine auto-selects
the best available backend at runtime.

## Architecture

    Apps -> UI Lib -> Browser Engine -> 2D Engine -> Backend

Backends (in priority order):
  1. Metal  — platform-native GPU rendering on Apple systems
  2. CUDA   — GPU-accelerated compute/offload via CUDA kernels (NVIDIA)
  3. ROCm/HIP — GPU-accelerated compute/offload for AMD GPUs
  4. Qualcomm — Adreno platform-native Vulkan delegate
  5. Vulkan — cross-platform GPU compute shaders
  6. OpenCL/OpenGL/Intel/WebGPU — secondary hardware paths
  7. Software / CPU SIMD / CPU — pure-Simple fallback paths
  8. Baremetal — OS framebuffer driver bridge (explicit only, not auto-detected)

## Quick Start

    use std.gpu.engine2d.{Engine2D}
    use std.gpu.engine2d.color.{rgb, color_white}

    var engine = Engine2D.create(800, 600)
    engine.clear(color_white())
    engine.draw_rect_filled(10, 10, 200, 100, rgb(255, 0, 0))
    engine.draw_text(20, 40, "Hello!", rgb(0, 0, 0), 14)
    engine.present()

## Layer Compositing

    use std.gpu.engine2d.compositor.{Compositor, Layer}

    var compositor = Compositor.create()
    var bg = Layer.create(0, 0, 800, 600)
    bg.fill(rgb(200, 200, 200))
    compositor.add_layer(bg)

    var fg = Layer.create(100, 100, 200, 200)
    fg.opacity = 0.7
    compositor.add_layer(fg)
    compositor.composite_to_buffer(engine.read_pixels(), 800, 600)

## Submodules

  - backend:          RenderBackend trait (combined Core + Adv)
  - backend_core:     RenderBackendCore trait (minimum required interface)
  - backend_adv:      RenderBackendAdv trait (optimized operations)
  - backend_lane:     Explicit drawing vs processing backend lane contract
  - backend_emu:      Stateless emulation layer (Core → Adv, no internal state)
  - backend_cpu:      Pure software CPU renderer (always available)
  - backend_cuda:     CUDA GPU renderer (NVIDIA GPUs)
  - backend_rocm:     ROCm/HIP GPU renderer (AMD GPUs)
  - backend_metal:    Metal GPU renderer (Apple GPUs)
  - backend_vulkan:   Vulkan GPU renderer (compute shaders)
  - backend_opengl:   OpenGL GPU renderer (FBO offscreen)
  - backend_intel:    Intel oneAPI GPU renderer (Intel GPUs)
  - backend_software: Optimized software renderer (tile-based, alpha blend)
  - backend_baremetal: OS framebuffer driver bridge (explicit selection only)
  - backend_virtio_gpu: VirtIO-GPU backend for QEMU (OS/baremetal only)
  - backend_webgpu:   WebGPU GPU renderer (V3 browser raster path, M7)
  - backend_qualcomm: Qualcomm Adreno backend (Vulkan delegate, Linux arm64)
  - backend_directx:  DirectX D3D11 backend (DXVK on Linux, native on Windows)
  - sffi_dispatch:     Dual-path SFFI dispatch (static extern fn + dynamic dlopen)
  - sffi_vulkan:       Vulkan SFFI dispatch class
  - sffi_cuda:         CUDA SFFI dispatch class
  - sffi_rocm:         ROCm/HIP SFFI dispatch class
  - sffi_intel:        Intel Level Zero SFFI dispatch class
  - simd_kernels:     SIMD-accelerated pixel operations (SSE4.2/AVX2/NEON)
  - generated_kernel_dispatch: compiler-emitted 2D kernel artifact metadata
  - vector_font_offload: typed vector-font offload/readback evidence
  - bitmap_font_offload: typed bitmap-font CPU glyph + GPU copy evidence
  - session_support:  Shared compute-session evidence/status helpers
  - draw_ir_adv:      Advanced Draw IR acceptor/executor with CPU fallback evidence
  - engine:           Engine2D facade with auto-detection
  - color:            Color packing, blending, interpolation, hex conversion
  - compositor:       Layer-based compositing with alpha blend
"""

# Re-export public API from submodules
use std.gpu.engine2d.engine.{Engine2D}
use std.gpu.engine2d.backend.{RenderBackend}
use std.gpu.engine2d.backend_core.{RenderBackendCore}
